{
  "texts": [
    "Answers, and CCTC Dataset, we extracted 1000 samples for each class.",
    "This choice was made to achieve a small but balanced dataset, as it has been observed that a small yet balanced dataset can yield models similar to those trained on the original data (Wang et al., 2016).",
    "Sampling 1000 samples per class significantly reduces the computational load while maintaining a reasonable impact on model performance.",
    "In the R2 dataset, we randomly selected 2,000 instances from each class, resulting in a total of 4000 instances.",
    "For the R5 dataset, we added the remaining three classes to the R2 dataset, totaling 6,803 instances."
  ]
}